abstract: Konstantin Sergeyev has been photographing residents of 155 Avenue C, commonly known as C-Squat, in Manhattan's East Village since 2000; building was first claimed by squatters in 1980s and will soon become legal property of its residents.
lead_paragraph: The now legal residents of C-Squat pay “house dues,” which go toward utility bills and payments on a bank loan.

headline.main: Photographs From the History of C-Squat, a Punk Homestead
